On Jul 5, 2007, at 6:33 PM, Douglas and Lori SWENSON wrote:

> I found an oil leak on my '76 Westy (there may be more). The  
> dipstick boot is
> torn. What is the best way the replace this? Do you just remove the  
> alternator
> belt and the cover that the tube runs through or is there more to it?

You can do it from below after you remove the lower tinware.

It can be a tough repair when the boots are stiff but the replacement  
boots are soft so you can bend them into place without having to move  
the dipstick tube.

> Just
> looking for advise before I start tearing things apart.

Be sure to get the Viton boot from VWG. It actually lasts vs. the  
others which crack from the heat in a few weeks.

http://www.airheadparts.com/viewDetail.asp?strMasterCat=&idproduct=6447

